The State moves to delete the repeater enhancer on count 2.  Motion granted.
The defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to the amended charge in count 2, possess Methamphetamine with intent to deliver.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3, possess heroin with intent to deliver as repeater and obstruct officer.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend nine (9) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 04-25-14 by 5:00 p.m.  Court authorizes release for AA meetings and treatment;
2) AODA assessment and follow through.
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) maintain fulltime employment or schooling;
7) provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) defendant is to speak to a high school in Manitowoc twice a year about dealing with drugs and the consequences.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Minutes.
